1. Paul Atkins' nomination as chairman of the US SEC has been voted through by the Senate Banking Committee;
2. The White House stressed that there is no room for negotiation on tariffs;
3. Coinbase submitted an application for XRP futures, which is expected to be launched on April 21, 2025;
4. The Babylon airdrop query page is now online;
5. A hearing to question the Federal Reserve Board is expected to be held next Thursday, involving the Federal Reserve's position on digital assets;
6. The number of initial jobless claims in the United States for the week ending March 29 was 219,000, and the expected number was 225,000;
7. Hyperlane announced the details of the airdrop, and 57% of the token supply will be allocated to the community;
8. Bitwise launched three option income strategy ETFs tracking Strategy, Coinbase and MARA;
9. U.S. stocks recorded their worst performance since September 2022, and global stock markets paid for Trump's tariff plan;
10. PsyFi will be launched on May 1 All services will be shut down on the same day, and users must withdraw funds before then;
11. Ethereum developers set May 7 as the target date for the Pectra upgrade;
12. Illinois will withdraw its pledge lawsuit against Coinbase.
